Layout {{{1

Block layout - vertically-biased
Inline layout - horizontally-biased

Image with float taller than its container: use clearfix
http://learnlayout.com/clearfix.html

Layout blocks left to right and wrapping
http://learnlayout.com/inline-block.html

FlexBox {{{2

2012 version: display: flex or flex-{*}
2011 version: display: flexbox or flex()
2009 version: display: box or box-{*}

http://www.sitepoint.com/easy-responsive-css-grid-layouts/
http://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/

Flex container properties
	display: -webkit-flex;
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: row (default) | column
	flex-wrap: nowrap (default) | wrap 
	flex-flow = direction || wrap (default row nowrap)
	justify-content: flex-start (default) | flex-end | center | 
		space-between (l & r stay at margins) | space-around (space between all)
	align-items: flex-start | flex-end | center | stretch (default) | baseline
	align-content (multi-line only)

Flex Item properties
	order
	flex-shrink
	flex-grow
	flex-basis
	flex = grow, shrink, basis
		http://css-tricks.com/almanac/properties/f/flex/



Media Queries {{{1

Device width depends on orientation
@media only screen and (max-width: 500px) {
min-width   True if screen at least x
            Minimum width at which these styles are shown
max-width   True if screen no bigger than x
            Maximum width at which these styles are shown


Semantic elements {{{1

article - self-contained content, makes sense on its own, must incl. heading
header -
	group of introductory & nav aides:
	- For page: Site title, logo, table of contents, search box
	- For section: heading, pub date, author, summary
nav - major navigation
section - group thematically related content with a heading
aside - tangentially related content
main - primary content of doc. Not child of article or sect.  Use with role="main" for IE compat.
